snippet.textDisplay: It's kind of sad that back in 2014 we thought Intel would have 10nm in late 2015 or early 2016. Mid to late 2020 is a full 5 years late. At the time they were about 2-3 years ahead of TSMC and Samsung in process tech. But now TSMC is at least 1-3 years ahead of Intel. TSMC closed a technological gap of about 10-12 years in 5-6 years while Intel got stuck. Impressive.
